      "description": "Presenting an exceptional 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a masterclass in lightweight JDM engineering. This survivor retains its factory-spec 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, delivering a seamless power band with no evidence of thermal degradation or vacuum circuit issues. The chassis features the original double-wishbone aluminum suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential, preserving the legendary 50/50 weight distribution. Mechanically flawless, the 5-speed manual transmission offers crisp synchronizer engagement, and the apex seals show optimal compression. Finished in its original paint with a pristine interior, this FD is an unmolested example of rotary perfection.",
